{{Infobox book <!-- |italic title = (see above) --> | name = Einstein Wrote Back | image = Einstein Wrote Back - bookcover.jpg | image_size = | caption = Hardcover edition | alt = | author = [[John Moffat (physicist)|John W. Moffat]] | title_orig = | translator = | illustrator = | cover_artist = | country = [[Canada]] | language = English | series = | subject = [[Memoir]] | genre = Non-fiction | publisher = | publisher2 = | pub_date = <!-- {{Start date|YYYY|MM|DD|df=y}} --> 2010 | english_pub_date = | media_type = | pages = 244 pp. | awards = | isbn = 978-0-88762-615-9 | oclc = | dewey = | congress = | preceded_by = [[Reinventing Gravity]] | preceded_by_quotation_marks = | followed_by = | followed_by_quotation_marks = | wikisource = }}
'''''Einstein Wrote Back''''' is a [[memoir]] by [[Canadians|Canadian]] [[physicist]] [[John Moffat (physicist)|John Moffat]] which documents his encounters with various other famous physicists, including [[Niels Bohr]], [[Albert Einstein]], [[Erwin Schrödinger]], [[Fred Hoyle]], [[Wolfgang Pauli]], [[Paul Dirac]], [[Abdus Salam]], and [[J. Robert Oppenheimer]], as well as his work at [[Imperial College London]], [[Princeton University]], [[CERN]], and the [[University of Toronto]].
==Title origin== The title of the book comes from a series of letters Moffat exchanged with Einstein early in his life, which inspired Moffat to continue studying physics.
==See also== *[[Reinventing Gravity]], another book by Moffat
[[Category:Physics books]] [[Category:Memoirs]]
{{physics-book-stub}} {{memoir-stub}}

'''George V. Eleftheriades''' does pioneering research in the field of [[metamaterials]]. He has been endowed with a [[Canada Research Chair]] at the [[University of Toronto]] and is a professor in the Department of [[Electrical engineering|Computer and Electrical Engineering]] there. He has received notable awards for his achievements, is a fellow of the [[IEEE Fellow|IEEE]] and the [[Fellow of the Royal Society of Canada|Royal Society of Canada]].
Also, at the University of Toronto, he heads a group for research in novel electromagnetic materials. He has also contributed book chapters to several books on [[antennas]] and [[transmission line|transmission line theory]] that utilize metamaterials, along with other novel concepts, and is co-editor of one book in the same field. Professor Eleftheriades is also the author and co-author of a significant volume of published [[research]] in [[peer review]]ed journals.<ref name=biopg/><ref name=proj/><ref name=books> {{cite web | title =Publications - Books, Journal, and Letter Publications | publisher =University of Toronto | date = | url =http://www.waves.utoronto.ca/prof/gelefth/Publications.html | accessdate =2012-01-12}}</ref><ref>*[https://books.google.com/books?id=l58lrWpI8LYC Negative-refraction Metamaterials: Fundamental Principles and Applications] By George V. Eleftheriades, Keith G. Balmain. Wiley-IEEE Press. {{ISBN|978-0-471-60146-3}} (Google Books)</ref>
== Awards and recognitions == Professor Eleftheriades was elected IEEE fellow "for contributions to conception, analysis and fabrication of electromagnetic materials and their applications."<ref name=ieee-bio> {{cite web | title =IEEE biography | publisher =IEEE Global History Network | date = | url =http://www.ieeeghn.org/wiki/index.php/George_V._Eleftheriades | accessdate =2012-01-12}}</ref><ref name=biopg> {{cite web | title =Short biography | publisher =University of Toronto | date = | url =http://www.waves.utoronto.ca/prof/gelefth/Eleftheriades.html | accessdate =2012-01-12}}</ref><ref name=chairs> {{cite web |title=Research Chiars |publisher=University of Toronto Faculty of Applied Science & Engineering |date= |url=http://www.engineering.utoronto.ca/Assets/AppSci+Digital+Assets/pdf/research+awards/researchchairs.pdf |accessdate=2012-01-12 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111128074822/http://www.engineering.utoronto.ca/Assets/AppSci+Digital+Assets/pdf/research+awards/researchchairs.pdf |archivedate=2011-11-28 |df= }} (description and awardees)</ref><ref name=group> {{cite web | title =Eleftheriades' Group | publisher =University of Toronto | date = | url =http://www.waves.utoronto.ca/prof/gelefth/main.html | accessdate =2012-01-12}}</ref><ref name=proj> {{cite web | title =Research projects | publisher =University of Toronto | date = | url =http://www.waves.utoronto.ca/prof/gelefth/Research.html | accessdate =2012-01-12}}</ref>
He received the 2008 [[IEEE Kiyo Tomiyasu Award]], a [[Institute of Electrical and Electronics Engineers#Technical field awards|Technical Field Award]] conferred by the [[IEEE]] Board of Directors.<ref>[http://www.ieee.org/documents/tomiyasu_rl.pdf List of recipients of the IEEE Kiyo Tomiyasu Award], [[IEEE]].</ref>
