{{notability|Companies|date=October 2013}}
{{unreferenced|date=October 2013}}
The '''Network of Concerned Anthropologists''' (NCA) is an independent ad hoc network of anthropologists seeking to promote an ethical [[anthropology]].

The network is concerned that the "[[war on terror]]" threatens to militarize anthropology in a way that undermines the integrity of the discipline. Therefore, the network offers the possibility to sign a [[Oath|pledge]] where it is stated what kinds of work anthropologists should not engage in.

The founding members of the Network of Concerned Anthropologists include Catherine Besteman, Andrew Bickford, Greg Feldman, Gustaaf Houtman, Roberto Gonzalez, [[Hugh Gusterson]], Jean Jackson, Kanhong Lin, [[Catherine Lutz]], [[David Price (anthropologist)|David Price]], and David Vine.<!-- As of September 2011 only two of these people have WP articles. Please do not redlink the other names.-->

