{{italic title}} {{Taxobox | name = ''Sphaerobacter'' | domain = [[Bacteria]] | phylum = [[Chloroflexi (phylum)|Chloroflexi]] | classis = [[Thermomicrobia]] | ordo = '''Sphaerobacterales''' | ordo_authority = Stackebrandt et al., 1997 | subordo = '''Sphaerobacterineae''' | subordo_authority = Garrity et al., 2003 | familia = '''Sphaerobacteraceae''' | familia_authority = Stackebrandt et al., 1997 | genus = '''''Sphaerobacter''''' | genus_authority = Demharter et al., 1989 | species = '''''S. thermophilus''''' | binomial = ''Sphaerobacter thermophilus'' | binomial_authority = Demharter et al., 1989 }}
'''''Sphaerobacter''''' is a genus of bacteria. When originally described it was placed in its own subclass (Spahaerobacteridae) within the class [[Actinobacteria]]. Subsequently, phylogenetic studies have now placed it in its own order '''Sphaerobacterales''' within the phylum [[Chloroflexi (phylum)|Chloroflexi]].<ref>{{cite journal |vauthors=Stackebrandt E, Rainey FA, Ward-Rainey NL | title = Proposal for a new hierarchic classification system, Actinobacteria classis nov. | journal = International Journal of Systematic Microbiology | year = 1997 | volume = 47 | pages = 479–491 | url=http://ijs.sgmjournals.org/cgi/content/abstract/47/2/479 | issue=2 | doi = 10.1099/00207713-47-2-479}}</ref><ref>Philip Hugenholtz and Erko Stackebrandt [http://ijs.sgmjournals.org/cgi/content/full/54/6/2049 ''Reclassification of Sphaerobacter thermophilus from the subclass Sphaerobacteridae in the phylum Actinobacteria to the class Thermomicrobia (emended description) in the phylum Chloroflexi (emended description)''] Int J Syst Evol Microbiol 54 (2004), 2049-2051; {{doi|10.1099/ijs.0.03028-0}} {{PMID|15545432}}; [http://ijs.sgmjournals.org/cgi/reprint/54/6/2049.pdf PDF]</ref> Up to now there is only one species of this genus known ('''''Sphaerobacter thermophilus''''').<ref>[http://www.bacterio.net/sphaerobacter.html LPSN bacterio.net]</ref>
